</div>
<style>
  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .suburb-form-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
  }
</style>
<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Albion's buyer pool is broader than many comparable inner north suburbs. Professionals working in Newstead and Fortitude Valley target it for the rail link and the proximity to the Valley's amenity without the Valley's noise. Downsizers from Ascot and Hamilton look at Albion for a lower entry point without fully stepping out of the inner ring. Investors are drawn by rental yield potential close to the employment precincts in Newstead and Bowen Hills. That breadth of demand types is an advantage for a well-run campaign: different buyers compete on different merits of the same property.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
