<!-- FAQ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:40px 24px 80px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Albion.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Albion Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Albion's character home market reflects its inner north position with direct rail to the CBD and a heritage precinct that supports strong owner-occupier interest. Prices vary meaningfully between the original cottage and Queenslander layer and the townhouse and development product closer to Sandgate Road. Contact Daniel for a current assessment of your specific property rather than relying on suburb-wide averages.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Albion?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Albion's diverse buyer pool means well-positioned homes attract attention from multiple buyer types at once: professionals targeting the rail link, downsizers comparing it to Ascot and Hamilton, and investors watching yields near Newstead. That competition, when the campaign is structured to reach all three groups, drives both pace and outcome. Correctly priced character homes typically generate strong campaign activity in the first two weeks.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Albion Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Albion is four kilometres from the CBD with a rail connection that makes it a genuinely commutable inner suburb. The Albion Mills precinct has brought food and lifestyle tenants to the suburb's heritage commercial buildings, and Fortitude Valley's full dining and entertainment offer is immediately south. Ascot's cafe strip along Sandgate Road is east. The residential streets behind the commercial corridor are quiet and predominantly owner-occupied, which is an uncommon combination at this proximity to the city.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What types of homes are in Albion?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Albion has a genuine mix: original character cottages and Queenslanders in the quieter residential streets, converted heritage buildings on and near Sandgate Road, and a layer of townhouses and newer development on the suburb's periphery. That variety means different buyers shop different parts of Albion for different reasons, and understanding which product type you own is important to positioning a campaign correctly.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

